-- Total Kenya Declines First Day in Three on Loss: Nairobi Mover
-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 2012-03-28T13:27:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-28/total-kenya-declines-first-day-in-three-on-loss-nairobi-mover.html
Total SA (FP) ’s Kenyan  unit  fell for the
first time in three days after the company posted an annual loss
from a profit a year earlier.  Total Kenya Ltd. (TKNL)  fell as much as 6 percent and traded 4.1
percent lower at 15.3 shillings as of the 3 p.m. close in
Nairobi.  The Nairobi-based company had a net loss of 71.4 million
shillings ($861,000) compared with a profit of 916.2 million
shillings a year earlier, according to an e-mailed statement
from the Nairobi Securities Exchange today. Revenue rose 33
percent to 105.6 billion shillings, it said.  “The usual challenges facing the oil industry such as
supply chain inefficiencies and price controls continue to
impact our performance,” the company said. Cost of sales rose
49 percent, it said.  The Kenyan government sets motor fuel and kerosene prices
once a month.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
